<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#00ff00" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShortBuss</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I followed all of the instruction for OE to the letter.  I did a full install of RH 7.2 and update to qt-3.0.1 as instructed.  I then compiled and ran OE.  I get the error message:<BR>pcap failed open: ioctl: No such device<P>I read the faq that was included and see that I need to update my pcap library.  Could someone please post instructions on how to do this?<P>By the way, I did run the tcpdump command, and was able to catch packets going to and from my gaming machine.<P>Thank you</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShortBuss</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I found the site <A HREF="http://www.tcdump.org" TARGET=_blank>www.tcdump.org</A>  and got the latest tar of the non beta version of both libpcap and tcpdump.  I expanded these into a directory, ran ./configure, make, and then make install.<BR>I tried running OE again after this, but still the same problem.  I then redownloaded OE and compiled it again.  I am still getting the same error message.  I checked the changes file in the libpcap that I downloaded, and it does support the "any" device as of 1/9/01.  According to the date, this feature should of already been in my build of Redhat 7.2.  Any idea what my problem could be?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">heiffer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">What does it say after that error message?  Can you post all the text?  I know sometimes mine will complain but, it still runs fine and says your build of OE is complete.<P>Did you do the ifconfig eth0 promisc and ulimit -c unlimited?<P>heiffer</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShortBuss</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thanks for the help.  The first time I tried this, before getting the pcap from <A HREF="http://www.tcpdump.org," TARGET=_blank>www.tcpdump.org,</A>  it did keep running, but nothing happened when I launched the game.<P>Now that I have updated pcap, it just gives the error message and terminates.<P>And yes, I did run both the ifconfig eth0 promisc and ulimit -c unlimited.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShortBuss</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I modified oeSniffer.cpp and changed the loading of "any" device to "eth0".  Now the program actually launches and starts listening.  I then launch the game and I start getting the error "Got non TCP/UDP packet" constantly.  This error message continues to scroll the screen until I quit, or OE crashes.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShortBuss</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I ran "tcpdump -i any", and it worked fine.  This means that "any" support is available in my pcap lib.  What else could be causing this problem?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShortBuss</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Just noticed that I have RH 7.1 installed, not 7.2.  I'll install 7.2 now and hope that fixes my problem.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShortBuss</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ok, got this working with the help of Maxzrz.  My first problem was I installed RH 7.1 instead of 7.2, so I did not have a recent enough libpcap.  I then downloaded and compiled the latest libpcap, but I did not remove the libpcap that was included in the rpms from the full install of RH.  I just had to remove the libpcap from the rpm and rebuild libpcap and OE, then everything works fine, on RH 7.1.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">frank2243242</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">try using odinseye.script found on in these threads...<P>it works fine updates all automagicaly and all<P>fixed all for me...<P>Exept now maps are fuket up with the glutessbeinpolygon wich affect 50% of maps...<P>weird...</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kreepin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yes, not having 7.2 will mess you up, i was wondering what was going on because i installed RH 7.2 and didnt have to upgrade Pcap</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lash</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You don't have to have redhat 7.2.  The only thing for sure besides the required libraries(read INSTALL.txt for them) is that your using a i386 based processor.  Redhat 7.2 for the newcomer is the least path of resistance for setting it up and redhat offers great support if you need it(buy the box to get it).  If your having a problem related to linux getting it installed, use a search engine.  There's a lot of help on linux out there if you look.<P>There are people running it on several different distro of linux like debian, slackware, and I think suse as well.  Some are even running it on redhat 6.2 fine.  Basically depends on your linux knowledge and preference which you should use.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
